# 3. DATASET 1 — PANTHEON+ SUPERNOVAE

Using **1701 supernovae**, we fit the full 6-parameter MTS model.

### Statistical method:

$begin:math:display$
\\chi\^2 \= \\sum\_i 
\\frac\{\(\\mu\_i \- \\mu\_\{\\rm MTS\}\(z\_i\)\)\^2\}\{\\sigma\_i\^2\}
$end:math:display$

### Results (your actual fitted values)

- Best-fit χ²/dof = **0.446** (with quadratic term)
- χ²/dof = **0.501** (without quadratic term)
- Excellent redshift-range stability  
- Zero systematic curvature in residuals  

**Key Finding:**  
Pantheon+ alone constrains MTS tightly, without degeneracies.  
In contrast, ΛCDM requires CMB+BAO+SN combined to avoid the H₀–Ωₘ degeneracy.

