# APPENDIX A — Mathematical Derivations (MTS)

## A1. Derivation of the MTS Comoving Distance Law

MTS assumes cosmic distances arise from a geometric response to motion rather than a Friedmann fluid expansion.  
The general MTS comoving distance is:

$begin:math:display$
d\_M\(z\) \= \\frac\{c\}\{H\_0\} \\\, \\frac\{z \(1 \+ \\tau z\)\}\{1 \+ \\alpha \\ln\(1\+z\) \+ \\beta z\}\,
$end:math:display$

where:
- $begin:math:text$ \\alpha $end:math:text$ — curvature memory  
- $begin:math:text$ \\beta $end:math:text$ — curvature flow  
- $begin:math:text$ \\tau \= \\text\{transition\} $end:math:text$ — motion–curvature turnover  

### A1.1 Low-z expansion

$begin:math:display$
1 \+ \\alpha \\ln\(1\+z\) \+ \\beta z
\= 1 \+ \(\\alpha \+ \\beta\)z \- \\tfrac\{1\}\{2\}\\alpha z\^2 \+ O\(z\^3\)
$end:math:display$

ΛCDM low-z expansion:

$begin:math:display$
d\_M\(z\) \= \\frac\{c\}\{H\_0\}\\left\[z \- \\frac\{1\}\{2\}\(1\+q\_0\)z\^2 \+ O\(z\^3\)\\right\]\.
$end:math:display$

Mapping:

$begin:math:display$
\\alpha \+ \\beta \\leftrightarrow \-q\_0\.
$end:math:display$

---

## A2. MTS Luminosity Distance

$begin:math:display$
d\_L\(z\) \= d\_M\(z\)\\left\[1 \+ h\\tanh\\left\(\\frac\{z\}\{\\tau\}\\right\) \+ qz\^2\\right\]\.
$end:math:display$

$begin:math:display$
\\mu\(z\) \= 5\\log\_\{10\}d\_L\(z\) \+ 25\.
$end:math:display$

---

## A3. BAO Distance Relations

$begin:math:display$
D\_M\(z\) \= d\_M\(z\)
$end:math:display$

$begin:math:display$
D\_A\(z\) \= \\frac\{D\_M\(z\)\}\{1\+z\}
$end:math:display$

$begin:math:display$
H\(z\) \= \\frac\{c\}\{dD\_M\/dz\}
$end:math:display$

$begin:math:display$
D\_V\(z\) \= \\left\[\(1\+z\)\^2 D\_A\^2 \\frac\{cz\}\{H\(z\)\}\\right\]\^\{1\/3\}
$end:math:display$

---

## A4. CMB Acoustic Scale

$begin:math:display$
D\_A\(z\_\{ls\}\) \= \\frac\{d\_M\(z\_\{ls\}\)\}\{1 \+ z\_\{ls\}\}
$end:math:display$

$begin:math:display$
\\ell\_1 \= \\frac\{\\pi D\_A\(z\_\{ls\}\)\}\{r\_s\}\.
$end:math:display$

---

# APPENDIX B — Computational Methodology (MTS)

## B1. χ² Minimization

Supernovae:
$begin:math:display$
\\chi\^2\_\{\\rm SN\} \= \\sum\_i \\frac\{\(\\mu\_i \- \\mu\_\{\\rm MTS\}\(z\_i\)\)\^2\}\{\\sigma\_i\^2\}
$end:math:display$

BAO:
$begin:math:display$
\\chi\^2\_\{\\rm BAO\} \=
\\sum\_j \\left\[
\\frac\{\(D\_M\^\{obs\}\-D\_M\)\^2\}\{\\sigma\_\{DM\}\^2\}
\+ \\frac\{\(H\^\{obs\}\-H\)\^2\}\{\\sigma\_H\^2\}
\+ \\frac\{\(D\_V\^\{obs\}\-D\_V\)\^2\}\{\\sigma\_\{DV\}\^2\}
\\right\]
$end:math:display$

CMB:
$begin:math:display$
\\chi\^2\_\{\\rm CMB\} \= \\frac\{\(\\ell\_1\^\{obs\} \- \\ell\_1\^\{MTS\}\)\^2\}\{\\sigma\_\\ell\^2\}
$end:math:display$

